Build a Report in Lightning Experience

Lightning Report Builder is a powerful tool for analyzing your Salesforce data. Group, filter, and summarize records to answer business questions.

REQUIRED EDITIONS AND USER PERMISSIONS
Available in: Lightning Experience, Essentials, Group, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, Developer Editions
To create, edit, and delete reports: Create and Customize Reports

On the Analytics tab, select Create | Report. Choose a report type and click Start Report.
Select fields to display data and group by rows and columns. Add filters as needed.

The report opens in edit mode with a preview. In edit mode:
Add and remove fields to your report as columns
Group records in your report
Filter report data
Add a chart

Customize your report until it shows the data that you need.
To add a column, choose a field in the Add column dropdown.
To summarize a column, select Summarize from the preview pane.

To group records, choose a field in the Add group dropdown. You can show or hide detail rows and totals.

After grouping records by a date field, customize date granularity.
To ungroup records, find the group you'd like to ungroup and click .
Removing a group also removes the column from your report. If you still want to show the column, add it back.

Click Save. Give the report a name and save it in an appropriate folder.
To view the report results, click Run.
